            <crm:P78_is_identified_by> He is a saint commemorated on 3 Maskaram who lived in the 14th century or 16th century. 
                  He is known as the founder of the monastery of Ḥāzalo
                  in Eritrea. 
                  
                     ʾabbā  ʾAnbas 
                  was one of the 33 disciples of 
                  
                     ʾabuna Takla Hāymānot I.                     
